{
  "id": "phekb-carotid-atherosclerosis-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "carotid-atherosclerosis",
  "name": "Carotid Atherosclerosis - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying all CAAD patients across the system using multi-resource evidence: Condition (carotid stenosis dx), MedicationRequest (antiplatelet/statin), Procedure (carotid revascularization). Some patients have only meds (Path C — empirical CV risk reduction without coded carotid disease).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete carotid atherosclerosis patient population for a vascular medicine quality initiative. Some patients have a coded diagnosis of carotid artery stenosis. Others were started on antiplatelet therapy (aspirin, clopidogrel) and statins (atorvastatin) for cardiovascular risk reduction without ever getting a formal carotid diagnosis. A subset has undergone carotid revascularization. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis, medications, and procedures — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with carotid disease.",
    "broad": "Find all patients with carotid atherosclerosis — by diagnosis, antiplatelet/statin meds, or carotid revascularization. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run three queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|64586002 — carotid stenosis dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1191,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|32968,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|83367 — antiplatelets + statin. (3) Procedure?code=http://snomed.info/sct|233259003 — carotid revascularization. Union the patient IDs."
  },
